Program: Omnibus
Title: Sister Elaine
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376l2l
Last Broadcast Date: 24 August 1995
Sister Elaine MacInnes talks about her extraordinary life and career. She has been a classical musician, catholic nun, has trained as a Zen Roshi in Japan, worked as an activist during civil war in the Philippines, and has campaigned to get meditation teachers into prisons across Canada. Picture: Zen mediation against sunset, Credit: Thinkstock Show less